The following module was proposed for inclusion in the Module List:

  modid:       App::Git::HomeSync
  DSLIP:       cdpnp
  description: Sync your home directory with Git
  userid:      TSTANTON (Tommy Stanton)
  chapterid:   23 (Miscellaneous_Modules)
  communities:
    AnnArbor.pm, LosAngeles.pm, ThousandOaks.pm

  similar:

  rationale:

    A program provided by this distribution, "git-home-sync", is used
    to automate the git/system commands necessary to get a user's home
    directory to be synced with a git repository. This allows the user
    to track things like dot files, making them available on a brand new
    machine. For example, your ~/.vimrc and/or ~/.emacs will always be
    the same on all machines that you use.

    For more background information, see
    "20100430-Tommy_Stanton-Sync_Your_~_With_Git" at:
    http://tommystanton.com/presentations/

    Also, a good article on this idea is at:
    http://joey.kitenet.net/svnhome/

    Quotes from the article: "I don't care if it's a PC clone, or a
    Mac, or a S/390 virtual machine; if it's not set up the same as all
    the others, if I cannot concentrate on the important differences
    instead of being distracted by the unimportant differences, then I
    will be less productive."

    "I actually keep most of my home directory in git now. Go figure.
    :-) I have not updated the above svn.kitenet.net urls, since
    references to git ones would not fit very well in the article, but
    see git.kitenet.net for the git versions of everything."

  enteredby:   TSTANTON (Tommy Stanton)
  enteredon:   Mon Aug 16 22:22:32 2010 GMT

The resulting entry would be:

